cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CC

The paper deals with learning algorithms for tree structures, which are commonly studied in computer science under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The focus on logical formulas and the aim for sublinear running time suggest a stronger association with machine learning and data structures, hence the higher likelihood of cs.LG and cs.DS. However, the paper also discusses the use of indexes and preprocessing, which are common techniques in databases and computational complexity. Therefore, cs.AI, cs.DB, and cs.CC are also likely sub-categories.
